#===============================================================================
# SCANMYPRIVACY BACKUP LOG DATABASE
#===============================================================================
# This file tracks all backup checkpoints with detailed comments and timestamps
# Like VSS (Visual SourceSafe) - Each entry is a restore point
#===============================================================================

#===============================================================================
# BACKUP ENTRY FORMAT:
#===============================================================================
# ID          : Sequential backup number (BACKUP-001, BACKUP-002, etc.)
# TIMESTAMP   : Date and time when backup was created (YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM:SS)
# GIT_HASH    : Git commit hash (short form for reference)
# AUTHOR      : Who created the backup
# TAGS        : Categories (FEATURE, BUGFIX, HOTFIX, RELEASE, MILESTONE)
# CHANGES     : Detailed list of what was added/modified/deleted
# FILES       : Specific files affected
# RESTORE_CMD : Command to restore to this checkpoint
# STATUS      : Current status (ACTIVE, RESTORED_FROM, DEPRECATED)
# NOTES       : Additional context or warnings
#===============================================================================

